<template><div><h1 id="path-root-regex" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#path-root-regex" aria-hidden="true">#</a> path-root-regex <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/path-root-regex" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/path-root-regex.svg?style=flat" alt="NPM version"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://npmjs.org/package/path-root-regex" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/path-root-regex.svg?style=flat" alt="NPM downloads"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://travis-ci.org/regexhq/path-root-regex" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/travis/regexhq/path-root-regex.svg?style=flat" alt="Build Status"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a></h1>
<blockquote>
<p>Regular expression for getting the root of a posix or windows filepath.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>You might also be interested in <a href="https://github.com/jonschlinkert/path-root" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">path-root<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>.</p>
<h2 id="usage" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#usage" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Usage</h2>
<p>The module exposes a function that must be called to get the regex (modified from the split device regex in the node.js path module);</p>
<div class="language-javascript ext-js line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-javascript"><code><span class="token keyword">var</span> pathRootRegex <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token function">require</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'path-root-regex'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

console<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">log</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token function">pathRootRegex</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token keyword">instanceof</span> <span class="token class-name">RegExp</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">//=> true</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p>See the <a href="https://github.com/jonschlinkert/path-root" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">path-root<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> module for examples.</p>
